WEBVTT

00:06.255 --> 00:08.464
Emily whoever took your son
never meant to hurt him.

00:08.714 --> 00:09.881
They just wanted money.

00:11.255 --> 00:12.130
(GUNSHOT)

00:12.214 --> 00:13.297
And something went...

00:13.381 --> 00:14.339
(YELLS)

00:14.422 --> 00:15.506
...horribly wrong.

00:16.047 --> 00:17.506
♪ (SINISTER MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:17.589 --> 00:20.214
Where were you the night
Charlie was taken, Mr. Dodson?

00:20.422 --> 00:21.964
Or should we call you
Mr. Baggerly?

00:22.255 --> 00:23.589
E.B. JONATHON:
Herman is your father?

00:23.673 --> 00:25.214
You're under arrest,
tough guy.

00:25.297 --> 00:26.255
Sister Alice,

00:26.506 --> 00:28.047
this is Matthew
and Emily Dodson.

00:28.130 --> 00:29.756
I saw your picture in the paper
and I said,

00:29.839 --> 00:31.631
"We must do everything
we can for them."

00:31.714 --> 00:33.756
Officer Drake,
there's something you gotta see.

00:34.547 --> 00:36.422
DETECTIVE: Reporting
mentions a blood trail.

00:36.506 --> 00:38.339
Yes sir, up the fire escape
to the roof.

00:38.756 --> 00:42.255
Could be the trail starts
on the roof and leads down.

00:45.589 --> 00:46.631
Who's George Gannon?

00:47.172 --> 00:49.172
"Love no one more than you.
Emily."

00:49.255 --> 00:50.297
I don't know anyone.

00:50.381 --> 00:51.381
Do not lie to me!

00:52.089 --> 00:53.756
She had nothing to do with
Charlie's murder.

00:53.839 --> 00:54.798
These letters say different.

00:54.881 --> 00:55.756
(CROWD CLAMORING)

00:56.297 --> 00:57.798
Emily Dodson you're under arrest
for the conspiracy kidnapping

00:57.881 --> 00:59.214
of Charlie Dodson.

01:00.089 --> 01:02.547
Criminal activity will be
quickly put down,

01:02.631 --> 01:06.047
and the laws energetically
enforced, to the benefit of all.

01:06.130 --> 01:07.130
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:13.464 --> 01:14.798
MAYNARD BARNES:
Gentlemen, gentlemen,

01:14.881 --> 01:18.381
I have here the purple prose
of a written correspondence

01:18.464 --> 01:21.547
between Charlie Dodson's
kidnapper, George Gannon,

01:21.631 --> 01:24.172
and his lover
and co-conspirator,

01:24.255 --> 01:26.381
the child's mother,
Emily Dodson.

01:26.464 --> 01:28.047
REPORTER 1:
Give us a look, come on.

01:28.130 --> 01:29.172
All right.

01:29.255 --> 01:30.839
We'll allow close-ups
in a moment.

01:30.923 --> 01:34.214
But gentlemen, I suggest
you warn your readers,

01:34.297 --> 01:36.589
because the thoughts
expressed therein

01:36.673 --> 01:39.047
are not for the pure of heart.

01:39.130 --> 01:40.255
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

01:40.339 --> 01:42.673
ELIAS BIRCHARD JONATHAN:
Co-conspirator, my shirt!

01:42.756 --> 01:45.214
They didn't have a thimble
of evidence when they arrested

01:45.297 --> 01:48.422
her husband for the same crime!

01:48.506 --> 01:51.422
I proved Matthew innocent
and I shall do the same

01:51.506 --> 01:52.756
for Emily.

01:52.839 --> 01:57.339
Those letters are mere
distraction and titillation!

01:57.422 --> 01:59.881
(LAUGHTER)

01:59.964 --> 02:03.547
Emily knew her husband
was the bastard son

02:03.631 --> 02:07.381
of a wealthy man
and she was angry

02:07.464 --> 02:09.589
she hadn't received
her piece of it.

02:09.673 --> 02:12.631
She expressed this
to George Gannon...

02:12.714 --> 02:14.964
DETECTIVE HOLCOMB:
...N-N-O-N, get it right.

02:15.047 --> 02:17.964
So the lovebirds worked up
a kidnapping scheme.

02:18.047 --> 02:20.631
George brought in two hoodlums
who had their own

02:20.714 --> 02:24.381
snatching ring in Milwaukee,
and, as you can see,

02:26.005 --> 02:27.506
there was a disagreement

02:27.589 --> 02:30.047
when, uh, it came time to
divvy up the ransom cash.

02:30.130 --> 02:32.673
-Saved us the price of a trial.
-(LAUGHTER)

02:32.756 --> 02:35.255
And so received
their just desserts?

02:35.339 --> 02:38.047
No, gentlemen.
For we, the people, were denied

02:38.130 --> 02:40.089
our right to judgment,
denied our duty

02:40.172 --> 02:43.422
to administer justice
as we see fit.

02:44.381 --> 02:46.255
All right, come on up,
get your shot,

02:46.339 --> 02:49.464
let the next guy get his,
you'll all get your turn.

02:49.547 --> 02:51.631
E.B.: It's all
part of the game, fellas.

02:51.714 --> 02:52.673
You know that.

02:52.756 --> 02:57.089
The D.A. expects us to play
the sap for him.

02:57.172 --> 03:00.589
But let's use our eyes,
let's use our heads.

03:01.214 --> 03:03.506
Emily Dodson's no killer.

03:03.589 --> 03:07.673
She's a hundred and three pounds
soaking wet, gentles.

03:07.756 --> 03:11.130
Kind neighbor,
devoutly religious,

03:11.631 --> 03:13.214
devoted wife.

03:13.297 --> 03:16.130
A whore?
No, I wouldn't say that.

03:16.214 --> 03:18.589
I've never heard of a whore
that killed her own baby.

03:18.673 --> 03:19.798
This is much worse.

03:19.881 --> 03:21.172
You're charging her with murder?

03:21.255 --> 03:23.506
Conspiracy kidnapping
which resulted in murder,

03:23.589 --> 03:27.130
but should we find it was
Emily's needlepoint

03:27.214 --> 03:28.881
that was used
on that blue-eyed boy,

03:28.964 --> 03:31.130
I'll strap on tap shoes
and add a murder charge,

03:31.214 --> 03:32.297
don't you doubt it.

03:32.381 --> 03:34.673
E.B.: She was conned
by some cons,

03:34.756 --> 03:37.964
and the only reason
she's sitting in jail now is...

03:38.047 --> 03:39.923
Jimmy, don't forget the neck.

03:40.005 --> 03:43.005
-I got the neck, no worries.
-Mm-hmm.

03:43.089 --> 03:45.589
Why hair grows there,
I'll never know.

03:46.464 --> 03:49.464
No, the only reason Emily's,
uh...

03:51.422 --> 03:52.631
She's what?

03:52.714 --> 03:53.881
Sitting in jail.

03:53.964 --> 03:56.381
She's sitting in jail
because the District Attorney

03:56.464 --> 03:59.297
is eyeballing the mayor's seat
and knows that corpses

03:59.381 --> 04:01.798
don't swing pretty
for a hungry electorate.

04:03.297 --> 04:06.047
BARNES: Her lawyer can rehearse
his defense in the paper

04:06.130 --> 04:10.381
all he wants.
I'll save mine for a sworn jury.

04:10.464 --> 04:12.381
Justice for Charlie Dodson.

04:12.464 --> 04:15.547
The noose for his mother!

04:15.631 --> 04:18.339
(FLASH BULBS POPPING)

04:18.422 --> 04:19.506
Got it?

04:19.589 --> 04:20.631
Let's go.

04:20.714 --> 04:22.255
All right, be good, boys.

04:22.339 --> 04:24.714
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

04:24.798 --> 04:27.714
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

04:32.923 --> 04:36.589
God is gone,
I said to myself.

04:36.673 --> 04:39.005
God is gone.

04:40.798 --> 04:44.756
Near 12 years to the day,
leaning beside my mother,

04:44.839 --> 04:46.547
in a three-times broke down...

04:46.631 --> 04:48.130
Should I be expecting
another surprise today?

04:48.214 --> 04:50.297
SISTER ALICE MCKEEGAN:
...four-cylinder
Peterson Touring Car.

04:50.381 --> 04:51.464
It was just the two of us...

04:51.547 --> 04:54.255
I had a little heart-to-heart
with Sister Alice

04:54.339 --> 04:55.839
about going off script.

04:55.923 --> 04:57.964
SISTER ALICE:
...halfway home to Canada.

04:58.047 --> 05:02.839
That hot blue sky so heavy,

05:02.923 --> 05:04.047
pushing down.

05:04.130 --> 05:07.047
Hadn't seen a plate of meat
for months...

05:08.339 --> 05:09.923
Do you remember that day,
Mother?

05:12.547 --> 05:13.547
Surely do.

05:16.047 --> 05:19.923
Enough money for food or gas.

05:20.881 --> 05:22.547
We had to make a choice.

05:24.381 --> 05:26.172
And that thought...

05:26.255 --> 05:30.464
like a worm digging its way
into my ear,

05:30.547 --> 05:34.047
into my heart, into my soul...

05:36.714 --> 05:39.714
"God is gone."

05:43.756 --> 05:45.214
And suddenly,

05:45.756 --> 05:48.089
everything went quiet.

05:49.172 --> 05:50.964
And brothers and sisters,
when I say

05:51.047 --> 05:53.005
everything went quiet,

05:53.089 --> 05:58.005
I mean the wind, the crank
shaft on that Peterson,

05:58.089 --> 06:01.214
everything went
absolutely silent.

06:01.839 --> 06:03.297
Just as it is now.

06:04.255 --> 06:06.464
And then, just as suddenly...

06:07.130 --> 06:10.714
such a noise in my head.

06:10.798 --> 06:15.255
Like a great swarm of insects
shouting to one another,

06:15.339 --> 06:18.881
or a thousand trumpets
blaring in unison

06:18.964 --> 06:21.756
trying to flatten the world
into powder.

06:23.756 --> 06:27.422
I fell out of the car
going 25 miles an hour,

06:27.506 --> 06:30.631
broke my collarbone,
laid there,

06:30.714 --> 06:33.464
with the sound taking me over.

06:35.339 --> 06:40.255
That was the voice
of God I heard.

06:40.339 --> 06:44.547
Past all my doubt
and despair,

06:44.631 --> 06:46.214
there was a voice.

06:46.297 --> 06:51.798
Our Lord and Savior's voice
telling me to pick up my Bible,

06:52.464 --> 06:54.714
and head to Los Angeles,

06:54.798 --> 06:57.214
City of Angels.

06:57.297 --> 07:00.964
Actually, he said
El Pueblo de Nuestra Señora

07:01.047 --> 07:04.422
de la Reina de los Ángeles
de Porciúncula.

07:04.506 --> 07:06.172
(CROWD LAUGHS)

07:06.255 --> 07:10.589
That was, um...
That was some eulogy you gave

07:10.673 --> 07:14.422
at the funeral.
Blessed is the hangman.

07:14.506 --> 07:16.923
Big hats
in the congregation yesterday.

07:17.005 --> 07:20.047
Hats that sat there
while Emily was arrested.

07:20.130 --> 07:22.506
Nothing big in that, Mr. Mason.

07:25.631 --> 07:28.047
What's in the bottle?
Holy Spirit?

07:29.005 --> 07:31.172
Vitamins and saline.

07:33.339 --> 07:34.881
BIRDY MCKEEGAN:
I believe we made room

07:34.964 --> 07:37.339
in our schedule to talk
about George Gannon.

07:38.381 --> 07:40.005
PERRY MASON: Okay.

07:40.089 --> 07:44.255
Um, George was employed
by your church?

07:44.339 --> 07:46.964
BIRDY: Firstly, Mr. Mason,
we are horrified to know

07:47.047 --> 07:48.422
there was someone
under our roof

07:48.506 --> 07:50.214
capable of such acts of evil.

07:50.297 --> 07:51.673
It has shaken our church.

07:51.756 --> 07:52.881
It's shaken all of us.

07:52.964 --> 07:54.172
ELDER SEIDEL:
He had good references

07:54.255 --> 07:55.881
from his former employers.

07:55.964 --> 07:58.964
We plugged him in
wherever there was a hole.

07:59.047 --> 08:00.839
MASON: And what holes
other than Emily's

08:00.923 --> 08:02.381
was he plugging?

08:04.547 --> 08:05.547
I'm sorry.

08:06.881 --> 08:08.923
I have words
that outrun my head sometimes.

08:09.005 --> 08:10.673
I apologize.

08:10.756 --> 08:13.005
ELDER SEIDEL: Mr. Gannon
was helping us organize

08:13.089 --> 08:14.673
some of our charity drives.

08:14.756 --> 08:18.214
And he did some bookkeeping
whenever we were shorthanded.

08:18.297 --> 08:20.005
What sort of charity drives?

08:20.089 --> 08:22.964
BIRDY: We open our doors
to all kinds, Mr. Mason.

08:23.047 --> 08:25.839
Whatever they enter with,
we offer redemption

08:25.923 --> 08:27.673
through the unconditional love
of Christ.

08:27.756 --> 08:30.506
SISTER ALICE: You should come by
when you have an hour.

08:30.589 --> 08:32.506
I'm on 21 times a week.

08:32.589 --> 08:35.089
You should save that seat
for someone who's buying.

08:35.172 --> 08:36.756
Maybe you don't know
what you need

08:36.839 --> 08:40.214
-until you see it.
-Oh, I have seen it, sister.

08:40.297 --> 08:41.964
SISTER ALICE:
But you haven't felt it.

08:43.714 --> 08:45.631
Not in here.

08:45.714 --> 08:48.422
If you had, you wouldn't think
you were so alone.

08:51.673 --> 08:53.964
Is this when you tell me
you have a message

08:54.047 --> 08:55.631
from my dear departed mother?

08:55.714 --> 08:57.172
SISTER ALICE: I do.

08:57.255 --> 08:59.339
She said you should be ashamed
for leaving the house

08:59.422 --> 09:02.089
-with your nails like that.
-(MEMBERS CHUCKLE)

09:07.297 --> 09:11.214
Thank you for these, um...

09:11.297 --> 09:13.464
Is there someone in the choir
I can talk to?

09:13.547 --> 09:15.631
-That's where they met, right?
-God is with your work.

09:15.714 --> 09:17.673
God left me in France, sister.

09:17.756 --> 09:19.005
SISTER ALICE:
God is with you

09:19.089 --> 09:20.923
whether you acknowledge
Him or not.

09:27.964 --> 09:28.964
Thank you.

09:33.130 --> 09:35.464
(INAUDIBLE)

09:37.631 --> 09:40.589
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

09:40.673 --> 09:44.172
At the arraignment,
you'll be seated up front.

09:44.255 --> 09:47.422
This way, when Emily announces
to the judge

09:47.506 --> 09:50.923
that she's not guilty,
he'll see a husband

09:51.005 --> 09:53.839
supporting his wife.
That's very important.

09:54.464 --> 09:56.255
Do you understand?

09:56.339 --> 09:58.381
Now, we caught a break
with the judge.

09:58.464 --> 10:00.506
Fred Wright, he's an old friend.

10:00.589 --> 10:02.339
You'll be out
of this cell very soon.

10:02.422 --> 10:04.422
Now, Barbara here
will make certain

10:04.506 --> 10:07.297
that you're never alone.
That's her job.

10:07.381 --> 10:10.964
If any detectives
come and talk to you,

10:11.047 --> 10:15.255
just clam up and say you're
represented by counsel.

10:15.339 --> 10:16.923
And it's not legal
for them to try,

10:17.005 --> 10:20.798
but sometimes detectives
don't play fair,

10:21.798 --> 10:23.506
isn't that right,
Barbara?

10:24.464 --> 10:26.422
(LAUGHS) Stone-face Barbara.

10:26.506 --> 10:27.756
DELLA STREET:
Did you hear that, Emily?

10:27.839 --> 10:29.047
EMILY DODSON:
Yes. Yes, I heard.

10:29.130 --> 10:30.881
Did you fuck him in our bed?

10:32.422 --> 10:35.881
Let's save that for home talk,
shall we?

10:35.964 --> 10:38.297
-No.
-His bed?

10:38.381 --> 10:40.422
-It wasn't like that.
-You're a liar!

10:40.506 --> 10:41.964
EMILY: Yeah.
What about you?

10:42.047 --> 10:44.089
I'm at home stretching pennies

10:44.172 --> 10:45.839
-while you're gambling.
-Oh, cry me a river.

10:45.923 --> 10:47.297
-Not at home. Not--
-Charlie was missing

10:47.381 --> 10:49.964
for three days and you said
nothing about this George

10:50.047 --> 10:51.297
-son of a bitch...
-Enough of this...

10:51.381 --> 10:55.255
If you had said something,
maybe they could have saved him.

10:57.464 --> 11:01.005
They arrested me,
and you still said nothing.

11:01.089 --> 11:03.631
They put Charlie in the ground,
and I wasn't there!

11:03.714 --> 11:06.631
-You let strangers bury our son!
-Shut up.

11:06.714 --> 11:08.631
You killed our Charlie Boy!

11:08.714 --> 11:12.673
(SCREAMING)
Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!

11:12.756 --> 11:14.881
E.B.: Just focus
on the task at hand.

11:14.964 --> 11:17.172
Husband and wife, together.

11:17.255 --> 11:19.297
We'll--
We'll have you home tomorrow.

11:20.172 --> 11:21.589
The judge knows me.

11:25.005 --> 11:27.297
Matthew?
Get back here.

11:27.381 --> 11:29.839
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

11:29.923 --> 11:32.964
What the hell is George's body
even doing over at County?

11:33.047 --> 11:35.381
Well, as it happens,
his little love roost

11:35.464 --> 11:37.089
is situated
across the city line.

11:37.172 --> 11:40.130
So, Frank Nance got him,
and I got these guys.

11:41.631 --> 11:43.923
MASON:
This is the exit wound, yes?

11:44.005 --> 11:46.255
You gotta stop hanging around
so many stiffs.

11:46.339 --> 11:48.172
But yes, exit wound.

11:48.255 --> 11:49.798
What's Frank
saying about George?

11:49.881 --> 11:51.005
VIRGIL SHEETS: Not much.

11:51.089 --> 11:53.714
Blew his own head off
with a shotgun. Case closed.

11:55.339 --> 11:56.339
Hmm.

11:56.839 --> 11:58.047
Can we flip him?

11:58.130 --> 12:01.714
-Sure. Get his legs.
-PETE: Uh-uh.

12:01.798 --> 12:04.756
(SCOFFS) Well,
he won't hurt you, right?

12:04.839 --> 12:07.255
"Come on, Strick,
I thought we were friends.

12:07.339 --> 12:08.673
Put 'er there."

12:11.422 --> 12:13.798
Boys, he's a big fella.

12:15.047 --> 12:19.130
(GROANS)
All right, one, two, three.

12:23.798 --> 12:26.547
Did I ever tell you boys
about the night man we had?

12:26.631 --> 12:29.714
Used to dress up like a cherub,
you know, wings and everything,

12:29.798 --> 12:32.881
and when a particular stiff
caught his particular fancy,

12:32.964 --> 12:35.130
he'd do this whole ceremony,
see--

12:35.214 --> 12:36.798
-MASON: Verge.
-Yeah?

12:38.005 --> 12:40.422
-What the hell is that?
-VIRGIL: Oh. Well,

12:40.506 --> 12:42.756
the way I figure it,
guy's on the floor

12:42.839 --> 12:44.589
and someone stood on his throat.

12:44.673 --> 12:47.047
And squish goes your hyoid bone.

12:47.964 --> 12:49.714
Virgil, we're gonna need
their personals.

12:49.798 --> 12:51.255
VIRGIL: Yeah, only I can't.

12:51.339 --> 12:53.839
Detectives come
and bag the whole lot.

12:53.923 --> 12:55.297
MASON: Holcomb and Ennis?

12:55.381 --> 12:56.673
So I'm told.

12:56.756 --> 12:58.923
So that guy, you know,
the cherub guy?

12:59.005 --> 13:01.506
He does this whole ceremony,
you know, with the stiff

13:01.589 --> 13:02.756
and the wings and some
candles and--

13:02.839 --> 13:04.422
-We fucking done here yet?
-MASON: Yeah, yeah.

13:04.506 --> 13:05.589
Thanks, Verge.

13:05.673 --> 13:08.923
Uh, if you ever need a favor...

13:09.005 --> 13:10.881
-Sure. Okay.
-MASON: Yeah.

13:13.798 --> 13:15.130
Yeah. Never would've caught him

13:15.214 --> 13:16.798
if it weren't
for the mayonnaise.

13:18.172 --> 13:20.589
So, the D.A.'s story
is our man George

13:20.673 --> 13:23.339
walks into the apartment,
guns down the Polacks.

13:24.756 --> 13:27.589
PETE: Except the one
ain't properly dead.

13:27.673 --> 13:29.255
MASON: Right.
He's lying on the floor.

13:30.381 --> 13:31.422
So George...

13:32.547 --> 13:35.172
Makes applesauce
with his Florsheim.

13:35.255 --> 13:37.255
Then he runs home
and grabs a shotgun.

13:37.339 --> 13:38.547
Because he can't live
with the sin.

13:38.631 --> 13:41.381
What? And adds suicide
to his list of unforgivables?

13:42.881 --> 13:45.881
Our George was a complicated
little guy.

13:51.214 --> 13:53.422
I want you to chase down
those references.

13:53.506 --> 13:57.130
Maybe somebody can throw some
new light on our guy George.

13:57.214 --> 14:00.005
I'm gonna hunt for those
missing personal effects.

14:00.089 --> 14:02.422
Don't E.B.
want us bagging witnesses

14:02.506 --> 14:04.464
to talk nice
about the Dodsons?

14:04.547 --> 14:06.839
I'm shifting our priorities.

14:06.923 --> 14:09.756
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

14:10.297 --> 14:11.422
(PHONE RINGS)

14:11.506 --> 14:12.839
JOE MORTON: I don't care
what they told you.

14:12.923 --> 14:15.589
All the evidence from that
warehouse mess had been boxed up

14:15.673 --> 14:16.839
and hauled off to the D.A.

14:16.923 --> 14:18.381
I'm not talking about stuff
from the crime scene,

14:18.464 --> 14:19.714
they said their personals
had been bagged.

14:19.798 --> 14:21.839
Yeah, yeah, the clothes
and the wallets from the stiffs.

14:21.923 --> 14:23.047
I don't fucking have them.

14:23.130 --> 14:25.130
Hey. Find out where the hell
Broome and Williams are,

14:25.214 --> 14:26.506
-will ya?
-MASON: You still have

