29:26.964 --> 29:28.798
-Oh, look. This is for you.
-Thanks, sir.

29:28.881 --> 29:30.214
Happy New Year!

29:30.297 --> 29:33.964
♪ (SINGER SINGS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE) ♪

29:47.839 --> 29:49.839
Why, um...

29:51.130 --> 29:52.381
Why don't we take a break?

29:52.464 --> 29:54.547
I'll get us that bottle
for-- for midnight.

29:54.631 --> 29:55.923
-LENNY: Mason.
-LUPE: Really? Now?

29:56.005 --> 29:57.673
Al's ready, now.

29:59.422 --> 30:00.923
So, you are working.

30:01.714 --> 30:02.714
I have to.

30:05.464 --> 30:06.839
Cabrón.

30:06.923 --> 30:08.631
AL HOWARD:
I've heard about you, Mason.

30:08.714 --> 30:10.923
-Not all of it's bad.  (CHUCKLES)
-(MASON CHUCKLES)

30:13.673 --> 30:15.214
MASON: I'm working
the Dodson case.

30:15.297 --> 30:17.464
Oh. Yeah.

30:17.547 --> 30:18.923
Ugly stuff.

30:19.005 --> 30:20.839
Who stitches up a kid's eyes?

30:21.923 --> 30:23.464
D.A. says George Gannon did.

30:23.547 --> 30:25.047
AL: We must be reading
different papers.

30:25.130 --> 30:26.964
Seems to me he likes
the slut for it.

30:27.047 --> 30:28.839
Why did Gannon
stop working for you?

30:28.923 --> 30:30.673
AL: I suppose
it was God's will.

30:31.130 --> 30:33.005
You fired him?

30:33.089 --> 30:35.381
I never even noticed
he was here.

30:35.464 --> 30:37.547
And then one day,
he up and quits.

30:37.631 --> 30:40.214
Talking about den of iniquity,
wages of sin,

30:40.297 --> 30:42.547
what's true in the Bible,
blah blah.

30:42.631 --> 30:45.839
His cheap dentures flapping,
spit going everywhere.

30:45.923 --> 30:48.714
I wrote him a solid reference
just to get out of the rain.

30:51.422 --> 30:52.881
When George was here,
you ever see him

30:52.964 --> 30:53.964
hang around the hard types?

30:54.047 --> 30:56.339
AL: I'm quite choosy
about my counting room.

30:56.422 --> 30:58.756
I like them brainy
and dull as dishwater.

31:00.714 --> 31:02.089
Do you mind if I ask around?

31:02.172 --> 31:03.881
AL: Now why would I mind that?

31:07.714 --> 31:09.839
(GAMBLERS CHATTER)

31:09.923 --> 31:11.130
GAMBLER: Come on, ten.

31:14.381 --> 31:16.547
Does anyone?
Have you seen my, um--

31:16.631 --> 31:18.506
(GAMBLERS CHEER)

31:18.589 --> 31:21.339
(SPEAKING IN SPANISH)

31:21.422 --> 31:23.005
MASON: How much did you clear?

31:23.089 --> 31:25.506
Enough to buy
a shitty run-down dairy

31:25.589 --> 31:27.547
and turn it
into a second runaway.

31:27.631 --> 31:28.631
Oh.

31:29.881 --> 31:31.839
Oh, you can't be talking about
my dairy

31:31.923 --> 31:33.464
because that's
a historical monument.

31:33.547 --> 31:34.714
Oh, is that right?

31:34.798 --> 31:37.589
Yeah, six of the last seven
presidents made a pilgrimage

31:37.673 --> 31:40.381
just to taste Mason's
Certified Quality Milk.

31:40.464 --> 31:43.673
So, did you find your killer,
killer?

31:47.923 --> 31:49.673
I did all right for a night.

32:24.506 --> 32:26.839
MASON: You could just tell me
you like me.

32:33.005 --> 32:34.547
I want my kiss.

32:38.214 --> 32:39.339
Okay.

32:54.422 --> 32:55.923
How do you feel, Papi?

32:58.714 --> 32:59.714
Wet.

33:23.714 --> 33:25.047
(E.B. SIGHS)

33:25.130 --> 33:26.381
(THUD)

33:43.172 --> 33:46.464
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

34:04.089 --> 34:08.214
(CAR HONKING)

34:15.047 --> 34:17.297
(KNOCKS ON DOOR)

34:23.631 --> 34:24.714
(DOOR CLICKS)

34:24.798 --> 34:26.089
DELLA: E.B.?

34:26.547 --> 34:27.589
E.B.

34:28.714 --> 34:29.964
You ready to go?

34:33.005 --> 34:35.673
E.B.: Della. Of course.

34:37.381 --> 34:39.589
I was just, uh...

34:39.673 --> 34:41.089
I was just...

34:50.881 --> 34:55.339
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

34:58.964 --> 35:00.297
DRAKE:
I got nothing to say to you.

35:00.381 --> 35:02.005
MASON: I got a bunch
of your reports, Officer Drake,

35:02.089 --> 35:04.631
and not one of them reads
like that kidnapping write-up.

35:04.714 --> 35:06.839
You-- You've got an eye
for detail, you're thorough,

35:06.923 --> 35:09.464
you know exactly
what should be-- (GRUNTS)

35:09.547 --> 35:10.923
You nosy son of a bitch.

35:11.005 --> 35:12.839
You steer clear of me.
You got that?

35:14.923 --> 35:16.756
-MASON: Listen.
-Got nothing I want to hear

35:16.839 --> 35:18.422
-from you.
-So you're just gonna play

35:18.506 --> 35:20.255
nigger for the D.A.
and his boys, is that it?

35:20.339 --> 35:22.923
'Cause George Gannon ain't no
fucking killer and you know it.

35:23.005 --> 35:25.381
You saw something and you
changed something in that--

35:25.464 --> 35:26.506
(GRUNTS)

35:29.047 --> 35:31.631
(COUGHS)

35:31.714 --> 35:33.089
DRAKE: Do you see this?

35:33.172 --> 35:35.297
This means I can kick
your white ass dead

35:35.381 --> 35:37.881
and no one would say
a goddamn thing.

35:37.964 --> 35:40.130
Reckon that makes you
the nigger.

35:40.214 --> 35:43.422
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

36:05.255 --> 36:06.381
Confucius...

36:09.422 --> 36:11.839
what do you do with that thing
when you wanna eat soup?

36:18.964 --> 36:20.130
(DOOR BUZZES, CLICKS)

36:23.089 --> 36:25.589
Ladies, hey, what's for lunch?

36:27.798 --> 36:29.547
I'll go with her.

36:29.631 --> 36:32.589
You look like a likes-girls-
to-piss-on-him type.

36:33.089 --> 36:34.381
How do, Jin?

36:35.756 --> 36:37.673
You take a room today?

36:37.756 --> 36:40.005
Partner's got the engine
running outside,

36:40.089 --> 36:42.881
so, uh, just the paperwork.

36:50.714 --> 36:52.547
(WOMEN SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

37:00.798 --> 37:02.756
(SPEAKING IN MANDARIN)

37:06.381 --> 37:07.756
A little light.

37:10.631 --> 37:13.589
I can shut this place down
in a heartbeat.

37:14.214 --> 37:18.673
Mr. Woo Sing is not happy.

37:19.547 --> 37:21.172
Tell Mr. Woo not to worry.

37:21.255 --> 37:23.381
Police asking questions
about him

37:23.464 --> 37:26.839
at Lucky Lagoon last night.

37:26.923 --> 37:28.422
What police?

37:30.381 --> 37:33.130
Mason.
Something Mason.

37:34.881 --> 37:37.464
E.B.: Write the truth,
you'll sell twice the papers.

37:38.839 --> 37:40.297
They're squeezing
the negro cop, E.B.

37:40.381 --> 37:42.714
He is sitting on something,
I'd bet my house on it.

37:42.798 --> 37:44.964
Your house ain't worth
the nails holding it up.

37:45.047 --> 37:47.923
Della! For the 14th time,
will you get me

37:48.005 --> 37:49.506
Herman Baggerly on the phone?

37:49.589 --> 37:51.297
I've left him three messages
already!

37:51.381 --> 37:54.130
E.B.: Then that means you've
ignored me 11 times!

37:55.381 --> 37:58.923
Emily is withering away
in there, we need that bail!

37:59.005 --> 38:01.005
What did you get on Gannon?

38:02.297 --> 38:04.255
Your penmanship is atrocious.

38:04.339 --> 38:06.130
His church choir called him
wallpaper.

38:06.214 --> 38:07.881
He used to be an accountant

38:07.964 --> 38:09.005
at a desert casino.

38:09.089 --> 38:10.964
There is nothing about this man
that makes me--

38:11.047 --> 38:12.422
-Wallpaper?
-Chicago Tribune  calling, Chief.

38:12.506 --> 38:14.464
MASON: Point is I don't make him
for a throat-stomping gunman,

38:14.547 --> 38:15.756
and my gut tells me neither
does Drake.

38:15.839 --> 38:18.506
-Who's Drake?
-The cop that found the bodies!

38:20.422 --> 38:23.631
E.B.: So, what does the, uh,
mightiest paper

38:23.714 --> 38:26.047
in the Midwest want
with E.B. Jonathan?

38:26.130 --> 38:28.381
MAN: Emily Dodson
is a murdering gash

38:28.464 --> 38:30.839
who don't deserve nothing
but the noose.

38:32.589 --> 38:35.339
(YELLING) That was not
The Chicago Tribune,  Della!

38:36.255 --> 38:38.547
Della! Della!

38:40.839 --> 38:43.464
Sometimes I think
this is no longer my world.

38:43.547 --> 38:46.714
(PANTING)

38:52.547 --> 38:54.464
MASON: So...

38:54.547 --> 38:57.631
-my gut tells me Drake--
-E.B.: Your gut isn't running

38:57.714 --> 39:00.756
this show, boy-o.
I tell you what to do.

39:00.839 --> 39:02.297
I tell you what to bring me.

39:02.381 --> 39:04.005
You're making holes
in your soles

39:04.089 --> 39:07.130
chasing after things
that I can't use!

39:07.214 --> 39:10.714
Maynard is crucifying her
and it's having an effect.

39:10.798 --> 39:13.756
A jury is not gonna give
two cents

39:13.839 --> 39:16.798
for what some Negro flatfoot
thinks about dead gangsters

39:16.881 --> 39:18.547
who got
what was coming to them.

39:18.631 --> 39:21.506
-It's a simple case.
-Holcomb leaned on Drake

39:21.589 --> 39:23.589
-to change the--
-E.B.: I'm talking now!

39:23.673 --> 39:25.255
You work for me!

39:29.464 --> 39:31.422
You made me lose my thought.

39:32.464 --> 39:34.881
-A simple case?
-Thank you. Simple.

39:34.964 --> 39:38.464
Emily's in on it with Gannon
or she's not.

39:38.547 --> 39:41.047
Now this casino angle of yours

39:41.130 --> 39:42.506
may be something I can use.

39:42.589 --> 39:45.464
Did the Poles ever frequent
the place?

39:46.339 --> 39:47.381
What is it, Della?

39:47.464 --> 39:48.923
DELLA: It's from Mr. Baggerly.

39:49.005 --> 39:50.881
E.B.: (SIGHS) Finally.

39:50.964 --> 39:52.255
Bring it here.

39:53.464 --> 39:55.506
Are you getting enough sleep,
E.B.?

40:10.839 --> 40:12.339
I think we got fired.

40:12.422 --> 40:15.839
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

40:23.547 --> 40:25.005
CLARA DRAKE: That you, babe?

40:25.673 --> 40:26.631
Yeah.

40:26.714 --> 40:28.464
CLARA: I got something
to show you.

40:28.547 --> 40:31.005
♪ (MUSIC PLAYS OVER STEREO) ♪

40:35.339 --> 40:37.297
That kind of a day, huh?

40:38.005 --> 40:39.297
-Seems like.
-Hmm.

40:39.381 --> 40:43.005
Well, you just put your feet up
and take a look at this.

40:43.506 --> 40:45.172
Baby powder.

40:45.255 --> 40:47.464
Now I know your mama
used cornstarch.

40:47.547 --> 40:50.381
My mama used cornstarch.
Hell, every baby ass

40:50.464 --> 40:54.589
on this block dusted halfway
to a hushpuppy with that stuff.

40:54.673 --> 40:57.172
But I figured, what with all
the money we saved

40:57.255 --> 41:00.756
with getting all that free food,
we may as well just try it out.

41:00.839 --> 41:01.964
Smell it.

41:02.839 --> 41:04.339
It's real nice.

41:09.756 --> 41:12.172
Well, you must have one hell
of a nose.

41:13.381 --> 41:15.547
Shouldn't have taken that food.

41:15.631 --> 41:17.172
-What?
-DRAKE: Shouldn't have taken

41:17.255 --> 41:18.506
nothing from that man.

41:18.589 --> 41:21.589
-Oh, don't be silly.
-Clara, you seen him.

41:22.673 --> 41:25.297
-You see what he is.
-Yeah, I know what he is.

41:25.381 --> 41:27.005
Then how am I
supposed to eat it?

41:27.089 --> 41:28.464
CLARA: With a smile
and a thank you.

41:28.547 --> 41:29.964
'Cause we're lucky to have it.

41:30.047 --> 41:32.464
'Cause there's plenty of folks
out there who don't.

41:32.547 --> 41:33.547
It's not luck, Clara.

41:33.631 --> 41:36.047
He got his claws in us,
that's what this is.

41:37.464 --> 41:40.464
Baby, you gotta stop and think.

41:40.547 --> 41:42.381
DRAKE: I beat
a man down today, Clara.

41:42.464 --> 41:44.047
He weren't doing nothing,
just his job.

41:44.130 --> 41:47.005
Trying to find the truth
and I beat him down.

41:48.631 --> 41:50.214
I'm supposed to be police,
not some--

41:50.297 --> 41:52.214
What you're supposed to be
is my husband

41:52.297 --> 41:54.089
and a father to your child.

41:55.005 --> 41:56.964
Now, I don't know this man,

41:57.047 --> 41:58.923
and I don't care about him.

41:59.756 --> 42:01.381
I care about us.

42:02.839 --> 42:06.172
Paul, you got a good job.

42:06.255 --> 42:08.005
You are police.

42:08.089 --> 42:11.255
Not a porter, not a janitor,

42:11.339 --> 42:13.673
and not busting dirt back home.

42:13.756 --> 42:16.631
So if this peckerwood
son of a bitch wants to keep

42:16.714 --> 42:20.297
our bellies full in exchange
for you doing him a favor,

42:20.381 --> 42:21.422
you do it.

42:21.923 --> 42:22.923
Paul...

42:24.422 --> 42:25.839
you do it.

42:25.923 --> 42:29.631
Not for him.
You do it for us.

42:30.923 --> 42:34.297
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

42:43.839 --> 42:46.464
You need to tell me next time
you visit that girl.

42:47.506 --> 42:49.464
You know we're doing
Holy Miracle today.

42:50.130 --> 42:51.422
We're doing three times today,

42:51.506 --> 42:53.964
so you're gonna have
to suit up.

42:54.047 --> 42:55.547
SISTER ALICE:
I'm gonna kill someone

42:55.631 --> 42:57.506
-with that fishing rod one day.
-Wonderful.

42:57.589 --> 42:59.381
They can put you
in a jail cell

42:59.464 --> 43:01.255
with your best friend Emily.

43:01.339 --> 43:03.923
You have never seen
someone more forsaken.

43:04.714 --> 43:06.255
I tried reading,

43:06.339 --> 43:07.881
I tried prayer.

43:07.964 --> 43:10.589
Words would not come out
of her mouth.

43:10.673 --> 43:12.714
Maybe she has no words
because she's done

43:12.798 --> 43:14.547
the very thing
she's charged with.

43:15.339 --> 43:17.130
God is testing us, Mother.

43:17.214 --> 43:19.714
BIRDY:
No, you're just bored.

43:19.798 --> 43:21.798
And you found yourself
a new toy,

43:21.881 --> 43:24.255
a frog in a mason jar.

43:24.339 --> 43:26.339
It's lizards in Los Angeles.

43:30.839 --> 43:32.964
We had a murderer amongst us.

43:33.673 --> 43:34.923
She laid with that man.

43:35.005 --> 43:36.714
It's just my opinion,
I'm not forcing it

43:36.798 --> 43:38.673
on anyone in the assembly.

43:39.214 --> 43:40.714
You are the assembly.

43:40.798 --> 43:42.422
You are the Temple.

43:42.506 --> 43:45.005
You are every cornerstone
laid for every church

43:45.089 --> 43:47.422
-chapter we built.
-Don't say that.

43:47.506 --> 43:49.964
Even if it's true,
it's not helpful to hear that.

43:51.172 --> 43:53.547
I'm sorry.
I don't mean to pile it on.

43:54.214 --> 43:56.339
It's just-- It's just--

43:56.422 --> 43:58.255
It's my way of saying...

43:59.506 --> 44:02.214
this woman does not
walk the path of God.

44:02.297 --> 44:04.673
And we need to distance
ourselves from her,

44:06.172 --> 44:07.923
for all the wonder
we've made here.

44:08.381 --> 44:09.547
(KNOCKS ON DOOR)

44:12.381 --> 44:15.923
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:22.089 --> 44:23.506
E.B.: (SIGHS) You know...

44:25.214 --> 44:27.339
I wouldn't be here asking if--

44:27.422 --> 44:29.547
It's a no, E.B.

44:30.130 --> 44:31.964
I'm not ask--

44:32.047 --> 44:35.798
I'm not asking for a gift,
just a small-term loan

44:35.881 --> 44:39.381
since... everything
I've done for you.

44:39.464 --> 44:41.214
You're kidding, right?

44:41.839 --> 44:43.422
Escrow juggling bullshit.

44:43.506 --> 44:45.756
There's no reason to bring up
the particular past.

44:45.839 --> 44:47.422
But you nearly got us disbarred.

44:47.506 --> 44:50.839
I'm here as a courtesy,
maybe some hot gossip.

44:50.923 --> 44:54.089
All you've done for me.
Fuck off, E.B.

44:54.172 --> 44:56.589
Herman Baggerly has withdrawn
his support.

44:57.506 --> 44:59.089
Baggerly's out?

45:00.172 --> 45:01.214
Yeah.

45:02.464 --> 45:04.631
-Yeah.
-Jesus, man.

45:05.881 --> 45:07.422
E.B.: What kind of a lawyer
would I be

45:07.506 --> 45:09.756
if I can't get my client
out on bail?

45:09.839 --> 45:12.714
-Give the girl a plea.
-She didn't do it, Lyle.

45:20.422 --> 45:21.798
Maynard called me.

45:23.214 --> 45:25.381
Said he wanted to talk about
our, uh,

45:25.464 --> 45:28.297
-our old partnership.
-What?

45:28.964 --> 45:30.839
I told him that I was, uh,

45:30.923 --> 45:33.506
it was not in my interest
to discuss the past.

45:33.589 --> 45:37.214
But if he digs, you know
there's something there.

45:37.297 --> 45:39.547
E.B.: How about this?
Forget the loan.

45:39.631 --> 45:40.881
Put in a call to Judge Wright

45:40.964 --> 45:43.255
and see if you can pull
a bail reduction for me.

45:43.339 --> 45:45.047
LYLE: Jesus. Elias,
you're not listening.

45:45.130 --> 45:46.798
I can save this girl.

45:46.881 --> 45:48.381
You can what?

45:48.464 --> 45:49.964
I just need a little help.

45:51.172 --> 45:54.089
Elias, plead out the case.

45:55.089 --> 45:57.464
Don't fucking drag me into this.

45:59.839 --> 46:01.172
And don't call me again.

46:05.881 --> 46:08.214
HERMAN BAGGERLY: The kidnappers
had a detailed plan.

46:09.381 --> 46:10.964
They knew who you were,
where you were.

46:11.047 --> 46:13.214
Had it not been that night,
it would have been

46:13.297 --> 46:15.339
the one before
or the one after.

46:17.255 --> 46:20.255
You really think
Emily was a part of it?

46:20.339 --> 46:23.339
She laid with the man
that murdered your son.

46:24.214 --> 46:25.714
You heard her say guilty.

46:27.172 --> 46:28.964
Consider the cold light,
Matthew.

46:30.798 --> 46:32.673
I came home mean sometimes.

46:34.422 --> 46:36.631
Maybe that's why
she went with that guy.

46:36.714 --> 46:38.547
HERMAN:
It's in our blood.

46:39.506 --> 46:41.255
We have a weakness for...

46:42.381 --> 46:44.255
degenerate femininity.

46:45.964 --> 46:47.547
My mother was not a degenerate.

46:48.756 --> 46:50.297
While you were here
living it up,

46:50.381 --> 46:52.381
my mother and me,
we did with nothing.

46:52.923 --> 46:54.047
It's not easy...

46:54.130 --> 46:55.631
what we've been doing here.

46:55.714 --> 46:57.464
Wasn't easy, this deal.

46:57.547 --> 46:59.547
It was cowardly of me.

47:00.381 --> 47:01.839
It was not Christian,

47:01.923 --> 47:04.673
and I would like
to atone for that.

47:06.130 --> 47:07.756
I'd like to show you something.

47:21.381 --> 47:22.923
MATTHEW: What's this?

47:23.005 --> 47:25.214
HERMAN: The town of Girard.

47:26.089 --> 47:27.964
It's about 30 miles
from here

47:28.047 --> 47:30.589
in the western corner
of this very valley.

47:32.255 --> 47:34.756
Help me build a city of faith.

47:34.839 --> 47:36.798
Of family.

47:36.881 --> 47:39.631
Far from the corruption
of Los Angeles.

47:42.464 --> 47:44.047
BYSTANDER:
What's she doing here?

47:46.923 --> 47:48.631
DELLA: Good evening, Sergeant.

47:48.714 --> 47:51.297
Visiting hours are
from 7:00 AM to 5:00 PM--

47:51.381 --> 47:52.547
You know me.

47:52.631 --> 47:55.089
I have a document
for Mrs. Dodson to sign.

47:55.172 --> 47:56.631
SERGEANT: What kind of document?

47:56.714 --> 47:58.381
A new retainer agreement.

